---
layout: post
title: "The Rising Threat of Supply Chain Attacks"
date: 2024-12-18
categories: security
tags: [supply chain, security, vulnerability]
---

As software becomes more interconnected, supply chain attacks have emerged as a significant risk. These attacks target vulnerabilities in third-party software or libraries that your product relies on. Ensuring the integrity of your software supply chain involves vetting your dependencies, monitoring for suspicious activity, and implementing secure procurement practices. A single vulnerability in a third-party component can put your entire product at risk, so vigilance is essential.
